Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.redis.codec

Enum RESPType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<RESPType>
      • org.bluezoo.gumdrop.redis.codec.RESPType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<RESPType>
    public enum RESPType
extends java.lang.Enum<RESPType>
    RESP (Redis Serialization Protocol) data types.

    Each type is identified by a single-byte prefix in the wire format.

    Author:
    Chris Burdess

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • SIMPLE_STRING

        public static final RESPType SIMPLE_STRING
        Simple string, prefixed by '+'. Used for short, non-binary strings like "OK" or "PONG".

      • ERROR

        public static final RESPType ERROR
        Error, prefixed by '-'. Contains an error message, typically with an error type prefix.

      • INTEGER

        public static final RESPType INTEGER
        Integer, prefixed by ':'. A signed 64-bit integer.

      • BULK_STRING

        public static final RESPType BULK_STRING
        Bulk string, prefixed by '$'. A binary-safe string with explicit length. Can be null (represented as "$-1\r\n").

      • ARRAY

        public static final RESPType ARRAY
        Array, prefixed by '*'. An ordered collection of RESP values. Can be null (represented as "*-1\r\n").
